[
    {
        "content": "<p>What's the best way to introduce some kind of \"local notation\", e.g., say I want to prove things about a finite group <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>G</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">G</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">G</span></span></span></span> of order <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">n</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span></span></span></span>. Here <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">n</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span></span></span></span> is really just a shorthand to avoid typing <code>Fintype.card G</code> every time.</p>\n<p>I tried</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">G</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Group</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">G</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Fintype</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">G</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">         </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">â„•</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">G_card_n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Fintype</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">card</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">G</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">include</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">G_card_n</span>\n<span class=\"c1\">-- start proving theorems</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>But practicing a bit, it does not seem very convenient (one ends up invoking <code>G_card_n</code> at the start of each proof to replace <code>n</code>). I guess what I have in mind would be some kind of macro that would be replaced by <code>Fintype.card G</code> before building. It seems that Lean3 had a <code>local notation</code> command that worked this way (as far as I understand) but that has apparently been removed.</p>",
        "id": 482635046,
        "sender_full_name": "Yannick Seurin",
        "timestamp": 1731683790
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If you write <code>open Fintype (card)</code>, then you can use <code>card G</code> which is much shorter than <code>Fintype.card G</code></p>",
        "id": 482635772,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1731684008
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Also, what makes you say <code>local notation</code> is removed? I see hundreds of uses in mathlib</p>",
        "id": 482635887,
        "sender_full_name": "Ruben Van de Velde",
        "timestamp": 1731684048
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Maybe syntax has changed but </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">local</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">notation</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ss\">`n</span><span class=\"bp\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Fintype</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">card</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">G</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>does not seem to work in vscode</p>",
        "id": 482637175,
        "sender_full_name": "Yannick Seurin",
        "timestamp": 1731684366
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I get</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Text only\"><pre><span></span><code>unexpected token '`'; expected '=&gt;'\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 482637324,
        "sender_full_name": "Yannick Seurin",
        "timestamp": 1731684412
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>OK, found the correct new syntax</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">local</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">notation</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"n\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Fintype</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">card</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">G</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 482638237,
        "sender_full_name": "Yannick Seurin",
        "timestamp": 1731684658
    }
